Each year the electronic documents community produces better tools for creating and changing document elements, including text, illustrations, video, and animation. At the same time, the user interface community works to build interfaces that improve the quality of interaction by effectively presenting information to the user and making it easy to act on and manipulate that information, These efforts can be combined by using documents us user interfaces. We have implemented an architecture, EmbeddedButtons, that allows arbitrary document elements. managed by arbitrary editors, to behave as buttons [2].